{"id": "ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM", "rating": 4.6, "userRatingCount": 177, "displayName": {"text": "Damsot", "languageCode": "ko"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kd1FWODFlRWgxTkU5alFWUldhWEo1TkRWUWNrRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "??Spicy Eggplant 🍆\nThis flavor was recommended by my friend and it's really good! It's fragrant and spicy, and goes well with rice. I think I'll choose this one next time and make it even spicier.\n??Steak🐮\nThis is their popular one. Big chunks of beef with eggs, sesame, and scallions. It's hard to say it's not delicious, right? Haha. I don't really like the steak sauce they serve on the side. It's a bit sour and not my taste. It's still better with mustard.\n??Mackerel 🐟\nThis is mashed mackerel that has been fried until fragrant, mixed with rice, and can be eaten wrapped in seaweed. It's also very flavorful!\nEvery meal can be turned into a soup-rice dish by pouring the soup over the rice. Each meal comes with a side salad and soup, and they are all very distinctive and not disappointing at all! After the meal, they gave us a very cute Korean version of Yakult. I also want to take a few Dubai chocolate cookies away, they are really delicious🤤. It's easy to sell out on weekends, but it seems easier to buy on weekdays. It's a small and very cozy Korean store.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "??Spicy Eggplant 🍆\nThis flavor was recommended by my friend and it's really good! It's fragrant and spicy, and goes well with rice. I think I'll choose this one next time and make it even spicier.\n??Steak🐮\nThis is their popular one. Big chunks of beef with eggs, sesame, and scallions. It's hard to say it's not delicious, right? Haha. I don't really like the steak sauce they serve on the side. It's a bit sour and not my taste. It's still better with mustard.\n??Mackerel 🐟\nThis is mashed mackerel that has been fried until fragrant, mixed with rice, and can be eaten wrapped in seaweed. It's also very flavorful!\nEvery meal can be turned into a soup-rice dish by pouring the soup over the rice. Each meal comes with a side salad and soup, and they are all very distinctive and not disappointing at all! After the meal, they gave us a very cute Korean version of Yakult. I also want to take a few Dubai chocolate cookies away, they are really delicious🤤. It's easy to sell out on weekends, but it seems easier to buy on weekdays. It's a small and very cozy Korean store.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Angela zheng", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112891392941499596612/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEXBmmhT5vjAHAljc--3lqaGKxwt7u4N_NPFzEYtRqCqcpjA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-18T06:17:13.140334446Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kd1FWODFlRWgxTkU5alFWUldhWEo1TkRWUWNrRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kd1FWODFlRWgxTkU5alFWUldhWEo1TkRWUWNrRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7cfcca9320f:0x4301b27a10ffb785"}, {"name": "places/ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kWFEzbFNRbEpXVWpadGExaElWbk0zZERWd1ZtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I liked the steak rice pot here especially with the wasabi! But actually the raw fish(?) banchan on the side was my favorite with the rice. It was super flavorful and had good chewy texture. I ate 2 of my friends' portion of it. Their fried shrimp eggplant appetizer was also super yummy. I also tried my friend's vegetarian eggplant rice pot and thought it was tasty.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I liked the steak rice pot here especially with the wasabi! But actually the raw fish(?) banchan on the side was my favorite with the rice. It was super flavorful and had good chewy texture. I ate 2 of my friends' portion of it. Their fried shrimp eggplant appetizer was also super yummy. I also tried my friend's vegetarian eggplant rice pot and thought it was tasty.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Elaine Wang", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108149311943287199389/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULV3jTJ9wcLdbVooMhB0YHf-cWnf8R7T9Pu2c_tMQcF3dzPzq4Ww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-21T03:20:37.815696981Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kWFEzbFNRbEpXVWpadGExaElWbk0zZERWd1ZtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kWFEzbFNRbEpXVWpadGExaElWbk0zZERWd1ZtYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7cfcca9320f:0x4301b27a10ffb785"}, {"name": "places/ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sR2NXZEhPWEl6UzJkM01VRkNZMUZmYVU5bk9IYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Tried Damsot in Ktown – super popular in Korea with 50+ locations. We got the eel rice bowl and the steak rice bowl. You mix everything up, eat the rice, then pour barley tea into the leftover scorched rice, cover it, and let it soften. The eel was tender and flavorful, and the tea‑soaked crispy rice at the end was such a unique texture. The steak bowl was juicy too. Also had salmon sashimi – very fresh. They even gave us a Korean version of Yakult after the meal. Parking is tight on the street, but there's a lot downstairs – just ask them to validate.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Tried Damsot in Ktown – super popular in Korea with 50+ locations. We got the eel rice bowl and the steak rice bowl. You mix everything up, eat the rice, then pour barley tea into the leftover scorched rice, cover it, and let it soften. The eel was tender and flavorful, and the tea‑soaked crispy rice at the end was such a unique texture. The steak bowl was juicy too. Also had salmon sashimi – very fresh. They even gave us a Korean version of Yakult after the meal. Parking is tight on the street, but there's a lot downstairs – just ask them to validate.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Alice", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114991881790830575623/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLklDn_u3qaecRwmR7PkKPyIfVYCw4Qc27F88aOPI8u7NsoQA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-06-13T09:01:24.694414390Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sR2NXZEhPWEl6UzJkM01VRkNZMUZmYVU5bk9IYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sR2NXZEhPWEl6UzJkM01VRkNZMUZmYVU5bk9IYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7cfcca9320f:0x4301b27a10ffb785"}, {"name": "places/ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25SbFpTMVhkbVk0ZWxJNFRXbEdhSGxJTmt0TWVHYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Damsot just opened their first U.S. location and I had to experience it for myself — and I’m so glad I did.\n\nThis spot is known in Korea for their signature Korean pot rice, and the presentation alone sets the tone. Everything comes out hot, steaming, and full of flavor in a traditional stone pot that really elevates the experience.\n\nAs someone who is vegan, I appreciated that there are options that can be modified. I tried the spicy eggplant pot rice and the tofu with shishito peppers — just removing the meat and egg — and both dishes were incredibly satisfying. Rich, comforting, and layered with flavor without feeling like anything was missing.\n\nThey also had crispy fried tofu on the side and a smooth drink to finish, which brought everything together perfectly.\n\nThe experience felt thoughtful, warm, and elevated. Definitely a place I’ll be coming back to and recommending to anyone looking to explore Korean cuisine in a new way.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Damsot just opened their first U.S. location and I had to experience it for myself — and I’m so glad I did.\n\nThis spot is known in Korea for their signature Korean pot rice, and the presentation alone sets the tone. Everything comes out hot, steaming, and full of flavor in a traditional stone pot that really elevates the experience.\n\nAs someone who is vegan, I appreciated that there are options that can be modified. I tried the spicy eggplant pot rice and the tofu with shishito peppers — just removing the meat and egg — and both dishes were incredibly satisfying. Rich, comforting, and layered with flavor without feeling like anything was missing.\n\nThey also had crispy fried tofu on the side and a smooth drink to finish, which brought everything together perfectly.\n\nThe experience felt thoughtful, warm, and elevated. Definitely a place I’ll be coming back to and recommending to anyone looking to explore Korean cuisine in a new way.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Travis White", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117014535677048920398/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIUsNIPfkNyRRtFqbpy1EdLOdx8fDWdA1J3azUXKMPiKEeiiFQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-12T02:48:23.092684686Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25SbFpTMVhkbVk0ZWxJNFRXbEdhSGxJTmt0TWVHYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25SbFpTMVhkbVk0ZWxJNFRXbEdhSGxJTmt0TWVHYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7cfcca9320f:0x4301b27a10ffb785"}, {"name": "places/ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGMFdWZHVVRk5pTnpaMFRGVlZNMmxqVlRsU1FuYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "An extremely cost-effective restaurant! It mainly offers set meals, which is very suitable for people working nearby. The menu is also very diverse. This time, I and my friends ordered beef rice and sukiyaki pot. We all thought they were delicious! Personally, I really like fried chicken. It's not very expensive but very crispy.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "An extremely cost-effective restaurant! It mainly offers set meals, which is very suitable for people working nearby. The menu is also very diverse. This time, I and my friends ordered beef rice and sukiyaki pot. We all thought they were delicious! Personally, I really like fried chicken. It's not very expensive but very crispy.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Meiyi Jiang", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117759034124852517621/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIaVU5RhFAWyfQmQshIPytBG862fYLet6KEvkuHZFl0RSOzYA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-12T01:00:53.185106255Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGMFdWZHVVRk5pTnpaMFRGVlZNMmxqVlRsU1FuYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGMFdWZHVVRk5pTnpaMFRGVlZNMmxqVlRsU1FuYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c7cfcca9320f:0x4301b27a10ffb785"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJDzKpzM_HwoARhbf_EHqyAUM/photos/AWCwydiU-1wAvECyN5Fm4W3KTWK34ZFrmzmvhaaFz369-yuU2V-wm-SQE3GSZTcH7BQdIYbLZ7bwGU8Xo-6DwdHSI8En9Dzdi3p6UkpZ3gP9oy4jS0nLosxt9lV-C1Yri8xKgjq3HtdzUkoVcmvwSmnBcAfkefKUsZU-QhoIJfoVwOqIMf-3Lnq6i5u6PXLKcfOaNJVdQIg9FKNtW2Gd3Oitaib5IuWL38qglbfnXV211fE4pV81fAVWICB0reMDLk3A5tGrOmCZ_HQEonQHHUlSKVHMtU31I1gL9cnqznGRcnr4hAv8AvfqxaEKacsBhFB4Uz4tmbHnbUX-IW2UmPFL8xVutzLFRB6NRL9fQO5Q_gN0p35ZtMUjJpNfQBWVXGr1YVJbKXIlnkprf2bftwjRGF1dKqqoQzXpDubc1xodbBWEXbUViIlvHSMVLheVUA", "widthPx":